<div class="full-width-layout__article-copy-section light">
	<div class="full-width-layout__copy"><p><em>Thursday, March 19, 1:00 p.m. PT </em><b><a href="/blog/blog/gtc-2026-news/">🔗</a></b></p>
<h2 id="robots" class="wp-block-heading" style="font-size: 24px;"><b>Robots Rove GTC in Droves</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">GTC isn’t just a gathering place for AI developers and innovators — it’s a popular destination for robots of all kinds, from humanoids and robotic arms to quadrupeds and autonomous mobile robots (AMRs).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><b>Helpful Humanoids</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The AGIBOT humanoid greeted GTC attendees in the convention center. It was trained using </span><a href="./assets/developer.nvidia.com/isaac/sim"><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;NVIDIA Isaac Sim</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><a href="./assets/developer.nvidia.com/isaac/lab"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Isaac Lab</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div></div>

