<div class="full-width-layout__article-copy-section light">
	<div class="full-width-layout__copy"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Spectators gathered around Sentigent Technology’s diminutive Rovar X3 robot in the expo hall. This outdoor or indoor companion was trained in Isaac Lab and runs on NVIDIA Jetson.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Over a dozen AMRs from </span><a href="/case-studies/serve-robotics/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Serve Robotics</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> were seen throughout the GTC campus, delivering food during the keynote pregame at SAP Center and carrying swag all week that attendees could pick out. Serve robots are simulated in Isaac Sim and powered by NVIDIA Jetson Orin.&nbsp;</span></p>
