	<div class="full-width-layout__copy"><p><em>Friday, March 20, 5:00 p.m. PT </em><b><a href="/blog/blog/gtc-2026-news/">🔗</a></b></p>
<h2 id="nemotron-days" class="wp-block-heading" style="font-size: 24px;"><b>Nemotron Days: Building the Future of Agentic AI</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nemotron Days at GTC brought together developers, partners and the AI community to explore how next‑generation agents are built, deployed and scaled. The goal: help developers move from short‑lived chatbots to long‑running, autonomous agents built on open foundations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Through interactive sessions, demos and partner showcases, attendees got hands‑on experience with the </span><a href="/blog/blog/adobe-ai-agents-nvidia-wpp/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NVIDIA OpenShell</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> runtime, the </span><a href="/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NVIDIA AI‑Q Blueprint</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> powered by LangChain and </span><a href="/ai-data-science/foundation-models/nemotron/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">NVIDIA Nemotron</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> open models — core technologies shaping the future of agentic AI. The sessions guided developers through real-world examples of how to design and deploy adaptive, open source agents built to run continuously and learn over time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Collaboration was a central focus, with sessions featuring teams from Cursor, CodeRabbit and ServiceNow highlighting how Nemotron technologies are already enabling practical solutions across the agentic AI ecosystem.</span></p>
