<hr>
</div></div>

<div class="full-width-layout__article-copy-section light">
	<div class="full-width-layout__copy"><p><em>Friday, March 20, 11:00 a.m. PT </em><b><a href="/blog/blog/gtc-2026-news/">🔗</a></b></p>
<h2 id="mclaren" class="wp-block-heading" style="font-size: 24px;"><b>McLaren Kicks AI Physics, Agentic AI Into Gear for Automotive Simulation and Design</b></h2>
<p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Accelerating the Future of Automotive Engineering" width="1200" height="675" src="./assets/www.youtube.com/embed/beSq5Ohd18k?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">McLaren Automotive is </span><a href="/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">accelerating its future product development</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> by bringing AI physics and agentic AI directly into its design workflows.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In collaboration with Rescale and NVIDIA, McLaren is accelerating its high‑fidelity, interactive simulation capabilities to support the rapid exploration of new automotive concepts. The Rescale digital engineering platform, powered by NVIDIA AI infrastructure, orchestrates the complex simulation workloads from end to end.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Using engineering AI agents to automate pre- and post-processing simulation tasks, McLaren can now explore more design space, run complex tests significantly faster and tune car components with greater precision — in just minutes instead of days.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">McLaren’s workflow was on display on the GTC showfloor this week:</span></p>
